The country is the 121st country to launch their satellite into space, no one should therefore confuse ‘Varyag’ information with country exposure, it is an insult to the hard work the People’s Government of Seychelles is executing day after day.

With ‘Varyag’ you will have a great number of people who were hot between their legs, an insult of an embarrassing sort is always healthy for the dimwits and they will dwell into the matter and make much more of it. It is not in Seychelles best interest to have extra attention when we are already on the front pages. THERE IS NO NEED to create unnecessary light and to satisfy the hunger of aroused as we can say, rats.

Give it 5 years and ‘Varyag’ will be forgotten by the man in the street, it will not be a topic transformation and point hunting; some will confuse what they have cultured with the country’s progress and development. The country’s advancement and development will not be altered by Varyag regardless of the number of curve detection tools, equipment searching devices and research efforts used, submarine, airplanes or satellites.

The country has progressed under the leadership of President James Michel regardless of the superficial attention by the extinct push-button media; you only press the button to erase matters or to validate them.
